<Unit>
<Name> Umbilical link
<Comment> mark insert 1.0 mark current 1.0 text {We have two systems now: The development system (host) and the application system (target). 
} 1.0 text {I call them host and target in the tradition of embedded systems programming, where Holon derives from. 
} 2.0 text {Host and target are connected via a communication channel to the target interpreter.
} 3.0 text {
} 4.0 text {Press the Load button and see what happens in the Chess game. -- Holon sends the source of this unit (see below) as a script to the target interpreter
} 5.0 text {
} 6.0 text {See how easy it is to change a running application system when you develop in  Holon. 
} 7.0 text {I do it all the time, it's really handy. You can't get a faster edit-test cycle, I suppose.} 8.0 mark anchor 8.91 text {
} 8.91 text {
} 9.0 text {Try it: Change the script and press Load. } 10.0
