<Unit>
<Name> UmbilicalConnection
<Comment> mark insert 1.0 mark current 1.0 text {Holon applies a concept that is } 1.0 mark anchor 1.32 text {used in the development of embedded systems. The development system (host) communicates with a small monitor in the target system. This "umbilical" connection is used to load and read code in the target, start and test the program, substitute code in the running system, debug, etc. 
} 1.32 text {
} 2.0 text {Holon communicates with the application via the shared file holon.mon and the Monitor that is defined in the Main module. Tcl is very helpfull, all we need is a contact to the interpreter.
} 3.0 text {
} 4.0 text {When you press the Load button, the source of the current unit is written to the file holon.mon, replacing the previous content. The monitor recognizes that the file is updated and passes the text to the Tcl interpreter.
} 5.0 text {
